{"title_page": "Alush", "text_new": "'''Alush''' ({{lang-he-n|\u05d0\u05b8\u05dc\u05d5\u05bc\u05e9\u05c1}}) was one of the places, according to the Book of Numbers, the last before [[Rephidim]], at which the [[Israelite]]s rested in [[the Exodus]] on their way to [[biblical Mount Sinai|Mount Sinai]] ([[Book of Numbers|Numbers]] 33:13, 14). Alush was the end on the ninth stage recorded by Moses in Numbers. The ninth stage is the segment from Dophkah to Alish. <ref>See Numbers 33:13</ref>This location has not been exactly located, yet may have been near the shore of the [[Red Sea]]. A particular event that occurred here was the story in the Exodus where [[water flowed from a rock]].\n\n{{ExodusStation|[[Dophkah]]|[[Rephidim]]}}\n\n{{Eastons|Alush}}\n\n{{coord|28|46|N|33|24|E|source:kolossus-plwiki|display=title}}\n\n{{Tanakh-stub}}\n", "text_old": "'''Alush''' ({{lang-he-n|\u05d0\u05b8\u05dc\u05d5\u05bc\u05e9\u05c1}}) was one of the places, according to the Book of Numbers, the last before [[Rephidim]], at which the [[Israelite]]s rested in [[the Exodus]] on their way to [[biblical Mount Sinai|Mount Sinai]] ([[Book of Numbers|Numbers]] 33:13, 14). It was probably situated on the shore of the [[Red Sea]]. A particular event that occurred here was the story in the Exodus where [[water flowed from a rock]].\n\n{{ExodusStation|[[Dophkah]]|[[Rephidim]]}}\n\n{{Eastons|Alush}}\n\n{{coord|28|46|N|33|24|E|source:kolossus-plwiki|display=title}}\n\n{{Tanakh-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Rick3655", "label": "safe", "comment": "Added clarity to the subject and source", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alush"}
{"title_page": "Eudes Dagoulou", "text_new": "{{Infobox football biography\n| name               = Eudes Dagoulou\n| image               = \n| caption             = \n| fullname            = Eudes Cratia Dagoulou Koziade\n| birth_date          = {{birth date and age|1990|2|9}}\n| birth_place         = [[Bimbo, Central African Republic|Bimbo]], [[Central African Republic]]\n| height              = {{height|m=1.84}}\n| position            = [[Attacking midfielder]]\n| currentclub         = [[Kalamata F.C.|Kalamata]]\n| clubnumber          =  \n| youthyears1         = \n| youthclubs1         = \n| years1              = 2008\u20132010\n| clubs1              = [[Olympic Real de Bangui]]\n| caps1               = 55\n| goals1              = 12\n| years2              = 2010\u20132011\n| clubs2              = [[AS P\u00e9lican]]\n| caps2               = 12\n| goals2              = 2\n| years3              = 2011\u20132014\n| clubs3              = [[MC Oran]]\n| caps3               = 60\n| goals3              = 13\n| years4              = 2014\u20132016\n| clubs4              = [[ES Setif]]\n| caps4               = 40\n| goals4              = 5\n| years5              = 2016\n| clubs5              = [[Al-Wehda Club (Mecca)|Al-Wehda]]\n| caps5               = 6\n| goals5              = 0\n| years6              = 2017\u20132018\n| clubs6              = [[Burgan SC]]\n| caps6               = 0\n| goals6              = 0\n| years7              = 2018\u2013\n| clubs7              = [[Kalamata F.C.|Kalamata]]\n| caps7               = 0\n| goals7              = 0\n| nationalyears1      = 2010\u2013\n| nationalteam1       = [[Central African Republic national football team|Central African Republic]]\n| nationalcaps1       = 17\n| nationalgoals1      = 1\n| medaltemplates      = \n| club-update         = 11:30, September 23, 2016 (EST)\n| nationalteam-update = 28 March 2018\n}}\n\n'''Eudes Cratia Dagoulou Koziade''' (born 9 February 1990 in [[Bimbo, Central African Republic|Bimbo]]) is a [[Central African Republic]] [[football (soccer)|footballer]] who  plays for [[Gamma Ethniki]] club [[Kalamata F.C.|Kalamata]] as an [[attacking midfielder]].\n\n==Club career==\nOn August 28, 2011, Dagoulou signed for [[Algeria]]n club [[MC Oran]].<ref>[http://www.mouloudia.com/index.php?option=com_k2&view=item&id=47:lattaquant-international-centrafricain-eudes-dagoulou-est-arriv%C3%A9-en-alg%C3%A9rie EUDES DAGOULOU est arriv\u00e9 en Alg\u00e9rie !] - ''mouloudia.com''</ref> On September 29, 2011, he made his debut for the club as a starter in a league game against [[USM Alger]].<ref>[http://www.dzfoot.com/fiches/fiche2.php?fiche_id=5861 USMA 2\u20130 MCO (day 7)] - ''dzfoot.com''</ref>\n\n==International career ==\n\n===International goals===\n:''Scores and results list Central African Republic's goal tally first.''<ref name=\"NFT\">{{cite web|url=http://www.national-football-teams.com/player/39939/Eudes_Deco_Dagoulou.html|title=Dagoulou, Eudes 'Deco'|publisher=National Football Teams|accessdate=28 March 2018}}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size:100%;\"\n! No !! Date !! Venue !! Opponent !! Score !! Result !! Competition\n|-\n| 1. || 27 March 2018 || [[Stade de Marrakech]], [[Marrakesh]], [[Morocco]] || {{fb|KEN}} || align=center | '''2'''\u20131 || align=center | 3\u20132 || [[Exhibition game|Friendly]]\n|}\n\n==Honours==\n*Champion of the [[Central African Republic League]] for 3 times in 2000, 2001, 2004 with [[Olympic Real de Bangui]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{Soccerway}}\n* [http://www.footballdatabase.eu/football.joueurs.eudes.dagoulou.118851.fr.html Eudes Dagoulou profile - ''footballdatabase'']\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Dagoulou, Eudes}}\n[[Category:1990 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Ombella-M'Poko]]\n[[Category:Central African Republic footballers]]\n[[Category:Association football midfielders]]\n[[Category:Olympic Real de Bangui players]]\n[[Category:AS P\u00e9lican players]]\n[[Category:MC Oran players]]\n[[Category:ES S\u00e9tif players]]\n[[Category:Al-Wehda Club (Mecca) players]]\n[[Category:Burgan SC players]]\n[[Category:Gabon Championnat National D1 players]]\n[[Category:Algerian Ligue Professionnelle 1 players]]\n[[Category:Saudi Professional League players]]\n[[Category:Central African Republic international footballers]]\n[[Category:Central African Republic expatriate footballers]]\n[[Category:Central African Republic expatriate sportspeople in Gabon]]\n[[Category:Central African Republic expatriate sportspeople in Algeria]]\n[[Category:Central African Republic expatriate sportspeople in Saudi Arabia]]\n[[Category:Central African Republic expatriate sportspeople in Kuwait]]\n[[Category:Central African Republic expatriate sportspeople in Greece]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Gabon]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Algeria]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Saudi Arabia]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Kuwait]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Greece]]\n\n{{CentralAfricanRepublic-footy-bio-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox football biography\n| name               = Eudes Dagoulou\n| image               = \n| caption             = \n| fullname            = Eudes Cratia Dagoulou Koziade\n| birth_date          = {{birth date and age|1990|2|9}}\n| birth_place         = [[Bimbo, Central African Republic|Bimbo]], [[Central African Republic]]\n| height              = {{height|m=1.84}}\n| position            = [[Attacking midfielder]]\n| currentclub         = [[Kalamata F.C.|Kalamata]]\n| clubnumber          =  \n| youthyears1         = \n| youthclubs1         = \n| years1              = 2008\u20132010\n| clubs1              = [[Olympic Real de Bangui]]\n| caps1               = 55\n| goals1              = 12\n| years2              = 2010\u20132011\n| clubs2              = [[AS P\u00e9lican]]\n| caps2               = 12\n| goals2              = 2\n| years3              = 2011\u20132014\n| clubs3              = [[